Foundation.Extension_Mechanisms.TaggedVa.Foundation.Extension_Mechanisms.TaggedVa: Stub schema document which comprises the whole of GML

UML representation of the GML implementation; This is an implementation model, so W3C XML Schema simpleTypes are used as the types of attributes and as parent classes as appropriate. Application Schemas should use ISO classes where they exist in preference to components from the GML package. The GML Package is included to provide documentation and cross-references between the ISO model and GML implementation that may be convenient to users already familiar with GML; the name of the corresponding ISO class is provided as the value of the class *alias* property. Also, classes from the GML package may be used if there is no corresponding ISO UML class - in this mode the GML model provides "extensions" to the ISO base.

The association of an era with a stratotype is optional. In the GSSP approach recommended by ICS for the Global Geologic Timescale, Unit Stratotypes are not used. Rather, the association of an Era with geologic units and sections is indirect, via the association of an era with Boundaries, which are in turn tied to Stratotype Points, which occur within host Stratotype Sections. Note that the "German School" defines stratigraphic eras conceptually, without reference to stratotypes.
